main event: A tear-shaped, bluish white light with vapors following was observed by a witness on the flying bridge of the USS Skywatcher picket ship.
interesting points: The object appeared to burn out after about 10 seconds of observation.
The object moved from east to west at a true heading of 285 degrees, following the curve of the earth but not going beyond the horizon.
No radar contact was made on the object at the time of the sighting.
There was considerable air traffic in the area at the time.
The report was prepared by Staff Sergeant Donald E. Woods, Intelligence Division, Headquarters, New York Air Defense Sector, McGuire AFB, New Jersey.
sighted object: Tear-shaped, bluish white light with vapors
location: Flying bridge of USS Skywatcher picket ship, off the coast
witnesses: One witness, Seaman Lawrence, W.J., USN, USS Skywatcher
photographs: No photographs included in the report
